org.gcn.plinguacore.util

Class IndexedPriorityQueue<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gcn.plinguacore.util.IndexedPriorityQueue<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of elements held in this collection. It must implement Comparable
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class IndexedPriorityQueue<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    An indexed priority queue consists of:
    • A tree structure of ordered pairs of the form (i,t_i). This tree structure has the property that each parent has a lower t_i than either of its children
    • An index structure whose i-th element points to the position in the tree that contains element (i,t_i)
